subSubSection.paragraph:
Emended diagnosis.
Body uniformly brown (
Figs. 1–4
), including legs. Eye mound armed with two rows of seven spines (
Fig. 7a
). Abdominal scute with two to three blunt processes sharply marked in both sexes (
Figs. 3–4
, 
7
). Shaft of penis more than two times longer than alate portion (
Fig. 10
).
